name: Fan Rotom
flavorText: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
Ability1Text: If you have 9 or more Pokémon Tool cards in your discard pile, ignore all Energy in the attack cost of each of this Pokémon's attacks.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Shaymin
flavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Yungoos
flavorText: It wanders around in a never-ending search for food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustion and falls asleep on the spot.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Gumshoos
flavorText: It adores having Rattata and Raticate for dinner, but as it's diurnal, it never encounters them. This Pokémon boasts incredible patience.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. If you find a Pokémon there, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Oranguru
flavorText: Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.
Attack1Text: Put 3 cards from your discard pile on the bottom of your deck in any order.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Type: Null
flavorText: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Silvally-GX
Ability1Text: Your Basic Pokémon in play have no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Drampa
flavorText: This Pokémon is friendly to people and loves children most of all. It comes from deep in the mountains to play with children it likes in town.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

name: Leafeon-GX
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 50 damage from 1 of your Pokémon that has any Energy attached to it.
Attack2Text: For each of your Benched Basic Pokémon, search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Pheromosa-GX
Attack1Text: If you go first, you can use this attack on your first turn.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Glaceon-GX
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Pokémon-GX and Pokémon-EX in play, in their hand, and in their discard pile have no Abilities, except for Freezing Gaze.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Xurkitree-GX
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon that have any Special Energy attached to them.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Add a card you find there to their Prize cards face down. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Dawn Wings Necrozma-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent. Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Celesteela-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

name: Dusk Mane Necrozma-GX
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Dialga-GX
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Palkia-GX
Attack1Text: Move any number of Energy from your Benched Pokémon to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Lunala-GX
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Psychic Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't be healed during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Knock Out 1 of your opponent's Basic Pokémon that isn't a Pokémon-GX. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)
